news.title: Nashik: Property tax collection target reduced to Rs 130 crore
news.para: Apart from this, the civic body has also reduced the water tax collection target from Rs 60 crore to Rs 50 crore for the current financial year.

news.title: Illegal buildings in Hyderabad development body region to be razed
news.para: The memo issued by special chief secretary Arvind Kumar claims that a number of constructions, apartments, gated communities and layouts are coming up without HMDA’s permission.

news.title: Nagpur civic body bent on land user change, ignores protests
news.para: ​​The civic body did not hold hearings on the objections received, and cancelled the public notice, despite protests from people, including leader of opposition Devendra Fadnavis and former mayor Sandip Joshi etc.

news.title: Taxman rejects exemption on interest income of several housing societies
news.para: Housing societies have been claiming exemptions on income earned from other co-operatives, which in most cases is interest income on savings held in fixed deposits with co-operative banks.

news.title: I-T dept detects suspicious transactions of Rs 650 crore after raids on Surat-based group
news.para: The Central Board of Direct Taxes (CBDT), which frames policy for the tax department, said "parallel sets of books of account" were recovered during the operation.

news.title: No impact of omicron variant so far on property market: CREDAI
news.para: For the time being, CREDAI is not expecting any disruption in project construction pace and deliveries too shall go as committed unless there is a significant rise in the infections in the months to come.

news.title: As air improves, SC leaves it to govt to relax industry, construction bans
news.para: The government's newly created committee for air quality management will decide on representations made by various aggrieved stake holders within a week, a bench led by CJI N.V. Ramana said.

news.title: Godrej Properties acquires 100% stake in Yerwada Developers
news.para: The paid-up capital of YDPL is Rs 1 lakh. 10,000 equity shares of Rs 10 each, representing 100% paid-up equity share capital of YDPL are acquired.

news.title: Noida authority steps in, stalls plan to hike Jaypee Wish Town upkeep rate
news.para: In a communication, Authority’s additional CEO Neha Sharma directed the facility management group (FMG) of the developer, Jaiprakash Associates Limited, to stall the latest hike in upkeep charges till a meeting on the matter is held between Noida officials, the homebuyers and the FMG.

news.title: Greater Noida authority directs Gaur Atulyam's builder to plug seepage in flats, basements
news.para: The builder also handed over the long-pending Rs 3.63 crore interest-free maintenance security (IFMS) amount to the apartment owners assocation (AOA) of the complex.

news.title: Chinese central banker says market can handle developer debt
news.para: Fears of a default have rattled financial markets, but economists say the ruling Communist Party wants to avoid sending the wrong signal at a time when it is trying to force companies to cut high debt burdens.

news.title: Shriram Properties IPO subscribed 4.6 times on final day
news.para: On Tuesday, a day ahead of its IPO, Shriram Properties raised Rs 268.64 crore from anchor investors as it allocated 2,27,66,949 equity shares at Rs 118 apiece, according to a BSE circular.

news.title: SWAMIH Fund achieves another closure; revives project in Bhiwadi
news.para: Within a period of six months, SWAMIH funding has made it possible to complete the construction of 100 units in 2 towers of Oxirich Sunskriti II, out of 700 units across 6 towers, a tweet from Finance Ministry said.

news.title: Canada's CPP Investments bets on home rentals as mortgage rates climb
news.para: CPP Investments, which manages C$541.5 billion ($426.1 billion) in Canada's national pension fund, on Wednesday announced its first investment in single family rental homes via a U.S. joint venture with Greystar Real Estate Partners for a combined $840 million.

news.title: Report illegal sand mining and get reward of Rs 25,000: Punjab CM
news.para: He also asked the deputy commissioners to declare a reward of Rs 25000 if a proof is provided in video or any other form about any violation of the norms in this regard.
